The Western Cape Health Department has called on all unemployed nurses to apply for short term positions. This comes as hospitals across the province are buckling under the strain of COVID-19 cases. “Are you a nurse? We need your help to fight against COVID-19! The Western Cape Department of Health is calling on all nurses who are unemployed to apply for short term contract appointments to assist us. Can you help us? Please apply on the coronavirus website: http://coronavirus.westerncape.gov.za <https://protect-za.mimecast.com/s/-xpUCY6x0ZCkoEl7s0H2cv.” A new variant of the virus is spreading: